Sentencas: The thermal expansion, electrical conductivity and electrochemical properties of La0.7Sr0.3CuO3-delta-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-delta (LSCu-SDC) composite cathodes for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) were investigated.
Titulo: Thermal expansion and electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3CuO3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ composite cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The addition of SDC to LSCu matrix materials significantly reduced the thermal expansion mismatch between them.
Titulo: Thermal expansion and electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3CuO3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ composite cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: SDC also suppressed the LSCu grain growth and increased the porosity of the composite cathode.
Titulo: Thermal expansion and electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3CuO3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ composite cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The electrochemical performance of the interfaces between the porous LSCu-SDC composite cathode and dense SDC electrolyte was examined using AC impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Thermal expansion and electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3CuO3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ composite cathode for IT-SOFCs

Sentencas: The polarization resistance was significantly reduced from 0.62 Omega cm(2) for pure LSCu to 0.29 Omega cm(2) for LSCu-25 wt.% SDC under open circuit condition at 800 degrees C, showing that the La0.7Sr0.3CuO3-delta-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-delta composite cathode is very promising to be used as a new cathode for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Thermal expansion and electrochemical performance of La0.7Sr0.3CuO3-δ-Sm0.2Ce0.8O2-δ composite cathode for IT-SOFCs
